A bystander was reportedly injured during a cash-in-transit heist in Hillbrow on Thursday afternoon. According to Emerg-G-Med paramedics‚ the civilian and a security guard were injured in the attack. The guard was reported to be in a critical condition. Pictures posted on social media suggested that it was a Fidelity truck that was targeted. It was not immediately clear whether any cash had been taken. Police were not immediately available to comment‚ saying a statement would be released later on Thursday afternoon. This is a developing story.